      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NITRO PLUME (1) flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot and stuck on well despite missing the frame, finishing fourth over 515m this track in 30.13. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings four times from four attempts. Rates on top in this line up. CABAO KYANITE (3) could manage only third at Hobart last time but impressed when posting a head turning 16.01 over 278m at this track three starts ago. Expected to feature on best figures. STIPULATED (8) was resuming when finishing sixth at this track in a Grade 4 (16.72). Has a good record at this journey. The form out of last race has been strong. Key runner on best form. PACO (2) can fill a top-three spot.",
